title: Britain’s WWII codebreaking hub Bletchley Park given £1 million by Facebook
text: Bletchley Park has received a £1 million ($1.3 million) donation from Facebook to help it through the coronavirus pandemic.

title: Global watchdogs agree rules for stablecoins like Facebook's Libra
text: Central banks set out to regulate cross-border stablecoins like Facebook's planned Libra with a common approach on Tuesday, saying more rules may later be needed to ensure stability.

title: Why Facebook Stock Jumped Today
text: A recovering online ad market bodes well for the social media giant.

title: Facebook moderators reportedly complain about Covid risk in Dublin office
text: Contractors who moderate content for Facebook in Dublin have reportedly complained about poor working conditions, which they fear could increase their chances of catching the coronavirus.

title: 3 Stocks to Buy for the Long Term, Regardless of Market Conditions
text: Investors are facing extreme volatility thanks to the U.S. elections and the pandemic. There are stocks to buy even in this mess.

title: Facebook EU-US data transfer complaint: Schrems gets a judicial review of the Irish DPC’s procedure
text: Another twist in a multi-year complaint saga related to the legality of Facebook’s data transfers: European privacy campaigner, Max Schrems, has today been granted a judicial review of the Irish regulator’s handling of his complaint. He’s expecting the hearing to take place before the end of the year — and is hoping the action will, […]

title: Not all tech companies are the same, said NYTimes' Tom Friedman on regulation
text: Tom Friedman, New York Times foreign affairs columnist, joins "Squawk Box" to discuss how regulators in the U.S. and abroad are looking to crackdown on Big Tech.

title: Why the EU is drawing up a ‘hit list’ of major Big Tech players like Facebook and Google
text: The list will be skewed toward U.S. companies such as Facebook or Google, considering the dominant role they play in the global technology industry.

title: Apple, Google and Facebook could reportedly be put on EU 'hit list'
text: Regulators in the EU are reportedly drawing up a list of around 20 tech giants that they want to comply with tougher rules.

title: FT: The EU is taking aim at Big Tech with a "hit list" of tougher regulations
text: Javier Espinoza, correspondent for the Financial Times covering EU competition and digital policy, discusses his reporting on how regulators are making a "hit list" of up to 20 large internet companies, including Facebook and Google, that may face new rules aimed at curbing their market dominance.
